---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About — IA Field Notes" description="What this site is, who writes it, and why it exists.">
  <article style="max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 6rem 2rem 4rem;">
    <header style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
      <p style="font-family: 'Commit Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.65rem; color: var(--text-meta); letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
        About This Project
      </p>
      <h1 style="font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem); font-weight: 600; line-height: 1.2; color: var(--text-primary);">
        A Practitioner's <em style="color: var(--accent);">Working Notebook</em>
      </h1>
    </header>

    <div style="font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.75;">
      <p>
        IA Field Notes is an independent editorial site focused on practical AI adoption.
        It documents real observations from embedding AI tools — particularly GitHub Copilot
        and Microsoft's AI ecosystem — into daily professional work.
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.6rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-primary); margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
        What This Is
      </h2>
      <ul style="list-style: none; padding: 0;">
        <li style="padding: 0.5rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);">📓 Field notes from daily AI-assisted work</li>
        <li style="padding: 0.5rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);">🎯 Structured use case breakdowns</li>
        <li style="padding: 0.5rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);">📋 Step-by-step workflow guides</li>
        <li style="padding: 0.5rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);">💬 Tested prompt patterns</li>
        <li style="padding: 0.5rem 0;">📡 Timely analysis of AI updates</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.6rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-primary); margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
        What This Isn't
      </h2>
      <p>
        This isn't a product blog, marketing site, or official documentation. It's one practitioner's
        honest observations — including what doesn't work, what's overhyped, and what's genuinely useful.
        Think of it as lab notes, not press releases.
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.6rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-primary); margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
        The Approach
      </h2>
      <p>
        Every piece follows a consistent structure: observation, context, assessment. Field notes are
        timestamped with ISO week notation and categorized by topic. The goal is content that remains
        useful six months from now — not hot takes that expire in six days.
      </p>

      <div style="margin-top: 3rem; padding: 1.5rem; background: var(--bg-surface); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 12px; text-align: center;">
        <p style="font-family: 'Commit Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.7rem; color: var(--text-meta); letter-spacing: 0.05em;">
          Independent practitioner notes. Not official Microsoft guidance.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
